name: NetWitness Endpoint
description: This app supports executing various endpoint-based investigative and containment actions on RSA NetWitness Endpoint

max_ioc_for_scheduled_poll.description: Maximum Container (IOC) to ingest for the scheduled poll (Default: 5)

actions.description: Get scan data of an endpoint
actions.verbose: This action will return the latest scan results. If the latest scan was done with a specific category, the resulting scan results may not contain data for all categories. If the limit parameter is 0 or not specified, the action will fetch complete data of all categories and for any other valid value, the action will fetch data equal to the limit specified for each category. For a particular category, if the limit specified is greater than the available data, the action will fetch all data for that category.

limit.description: Maximum number of records to retrieve for each category (Default: 50)

actions.description: Action to ingest endpoint related information
actions.verbose:
This action ingests all the IOCs having OS type "Windows", IOC level max_ioc_level and lower and whose machine count and module count are greater than 0. The IOCs fetched are ordered concerning time. Containers are uniquely identified by IOC Description and its OS type. The information of affected machines and modules of an IOC is ingested as artifacts. During manual polling, the number of IOCs to be ingested can be controlled by container_count, and during scheduled polling, the number of IOCs to be ingested in each cycle can be controlled by max_ioc_for_scheduled_poll.

IOCArtifact NameCEF Field
FileFile ArtifactfileHashMd5, fileHashSha1, fileHashSha256, fileName, iiocScore, riskScore
Endpoint DetailsEndpoint ArtifactnweMachineGuid, sourceAddress, remoteAddress, sourceUserName, sourceMacAddress, iiocScore, machineName
Instant IOC DetailsInstant IOC ArtifactinstantIocName, iocLevel, iocType, lastExecutedTime, osType

container_count.description: Maximum number of containers to ingest

actions.verbose:
This action lists all IOCs having OS type "Windows".
The results are always sorted in ascending order based on their IOC level to place the most critical IOCs at the top. For example, to get the top 10 critical IOCs that matched the filter, specify the limit as 10. If the limit is zero, then all matching IOCs will be returned.

limit.description: Maximum number of IOCs to retrieve (Default: 50)

example_values:
SELECT DISTINCT
	[mp].[FK_Machines] AS [FK_Machines],
	[mp].[PK_MachineModulePaths] AS [FK_MachineModulePaths]           
FROM
	[dbo].[MachineModulePaths] AS [mp] WITH(NOLOCK)
	INNER JOIN [dbo].[MachinesToEvaluate] AS [me] WITH(NOLOCK) ON ([me].[RK_Machines] = [mp].[FK_Machines])
WHERE 
	[mp].[NetworkListen] = 1 AND
	[mp].[MarkedAsDeleted]  = 0
